{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"410aaa–81c","heading":"Prohibited uses of acquired, donated, and conservation land","label":"410aaa–81c Prohibited uses of acquired, donated, and conservation land","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch1/schLIX–Y/ptD","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe National Environmental Policy Act of 1969, referred to in subsec. (c)(1)(B), is , , , which is classified generally to chapter 55 (§ 4321 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 91–19083 Stat. 852section 4321 of Title 42Jan. 1, 1970","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","“Secretary” Definedprovided in part that in this subchapter “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior.Section 103 of Pub. L. 103–433"],"amendments":["References in TextThe National Environmental Policy Act of 1969, referred to in subsec. (c)(1)(B), is , , , which is classified generally to chapter 55 (§ 4321 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 91–19083 Stat. 852section 4321 of Title 42Jan. 1, 1970"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definitions","label":"a Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Acquired land","label":"1 Acquired land","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “acquired land” means any land acquired within the Conservation Area using amounts from the land and water conservation fund established under .section 200302 of title 54","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Conservation area","label":"2 Conservation area","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Conservation Area” means the California Desert Conservation Area.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Conservation land","label":"3 Conservation land","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"national conservation land established pursuant to ; andsection 7202(b)(2)(D) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"areas of critical environmental concern established pursuant to .section 1712(c)(3) of title 43","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Donated land","label":"4 Donated land","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “donated land” means any private land donated to the United States for conservation purposes in the Conservation Area.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Donor","label":"5 Donor","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “donor” means an individual or entity that donates private land within the Conservation Area to the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":"Secretary","label":"6 Secretary","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs410aaa%E2%80%9381c%2Fa%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Secretary” means the Secretary, acting through the Director of the Bureau of Land Management.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":"State","label":"7 State","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410aaa–81c/a","sour